==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Deadwood
<hw>Dead"wood`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A mass of timbers built into the bow and stern
of a vessel to give solidity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Dead trees or branches; useless material.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <mark>[fig.]</mark> <def>People who are unproductive; --
used especially in reference to employees.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Deadworks</ent>⟦br⟧
